  "prompt": "Does NASA recruit Indians?",
  "response": "Yes, NASA does recruit individuals from various countries, including India, provided they meet the necessary qualifications and legal requirements. Here\u2019s how Indians can potentially work with NASA:\n\n### 1. **As U.S. Citizens or Permanent Residents**\n   - Many positions at NASA require U.S. citizenship or permanent residency (Green Card) due to the sensitive nature of the work, particularly in areas related to national security and space technology. Indians who have become U.S. citizens or hold a Green Card are eligible to apply for such roles.\n\n### 2. **Through International Collaborations**\n   - NASA collaborates with space agencies and institutions worldwide, including the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO). Indian scientists, engineers, and researchers can participate in NASA-led projects through these collaborations.\n\n### 3. **Internships and Fellowships**\n   - NASA offers internships and fellowships to international students, including Indians, through specific programs. For example:\n     - The **NASA International Internship (NASA I\u00b2)** program allows international students to work on NASA projects. Applications are typically submitted through partner institutions or space agencies in the student\u2019s home country.\n     - The **Fulbright-Nehru Fellowship** enables Indian students and researchers to work with NASA on specific projects.\n\n### 4. **Research and Academic Partnerships**\n   - Indian researchers and academics can collaborate with NASA through joint research initiatives, publications, and conferences. NASA often partners with universities and research organizations globally, including in India.\n\n### 5. **Job Opportunities for Non-U.S. Citizens**\n   - For certain specialized roles, NASA may hire non-U.S. citizens if they possess unique skills or expertise that are not readily available among U.S. applicants. However, such opportunities are rare and highly competitive.\n\n### Steps to Explore Opportunities:\n   - Visit NASA\u2019s official careers website: [NASA Careers](https://www.nasa.gov/careers)\n   - Check for international internship and fellowship opportunities.\n   - Collaborate with Indian institutions involved in space research, such as ISRO, which often partners with NASA.\n\nIf you're an Indian aspiring to work with NASA, focus on building a strong academic and professional background in STEM (Science, Technology, Engineering, and Mathematics) fields, and explore opportunities for collaboration or immigration to the U.S. if required.",
